CommonFields.Location: Shanghai Key Laboratory of Electrical Insulation and Thermal Aging, Department of Polymer Science and Engineering, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Shanghai 200240, China

Heating.Description: mixed solution sealed in a 90mL Teflon autoclave and maintained in an oven

ChooseParameter.Other: resultant Na2Ti3O7 NWs were washed with deionized water and ethanol until pH-neutral
resultant NWs soaked in a 0.1 M hydrochloric acid aqueous solution for 12 h to produce hydrogen titanate (H2Ti3O7) NWs

Drying-Evaporation.Description: obtained H2Ti3O7 NWs were dried in a vacuum oven

Mixing.Description: Ba(OH)2·8H2O (0.804 g, 2.55 × 10−3 mol) and Sr(OH)2·8H2O (0.120 g, 0.45 × 10−3 mol) were added to H2Ti3O7 (0.129 g, 5 × 10−4 mol) to fully transform the H2Ti3O7 NWs to Ba0.7Sr0.3TiO3 NWs

ChooseParameter.Other: obtained NWs were rinsed several times with 0.1 M aqueous hydrochloric acid solution, deionized water, and ethanol

MoldingInfo.Description: mixture was cast on a glass plate

Drying-Evaporation.Description: films were kept under vacuum to remove the solvent thoroughly

MoldingInfo.Description: films were hot-pressed to produce samples of the desired thickness

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: applied to characterize the morphologies of the NWs and the nanocomposite samples.

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description: applied to characterize the morphologies of the NWs and the nanocomposite samples

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: used to measure dielectric properties over the frequency range 10^−1 - 10^6 Hz at room temperature

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: used to characterize the chemical structures of the pristine and surface-modified NWs over the range of 4000−400 cm^−1

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: rhe crystalline structured of the NWs were analyzed by XRD with a Cu K-alpha source

XRay_Photoelectron_Spectroscopy.Description: used with a monochromatized Al K-alpha source. A

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: used to perform TGA of NWs at a heating rate of 20C/min

Nuclear_Magnetic_Resonance.Description: used to record H NMR spectra of different samples

Electrometry.Equipment: dielectric strength tester with a ball-to-ball stainless electrode
Electrometry.Description: used to measure dielectric breakdown strength
